* listing by professions :
* software coder
	* mostly category theory
	* some very basic abstract algebra
	* not much else
* algorithm developer
	* may need any fields of math, depending on the topic of your product
	* very common for artificial intelligence and signal processing
		* functional analysis
		* linear algebra
		* probability theory
* programming language expert [student | enthusiast | designer | researcher]
	* all what a software coder needs
	* lambda calculus, combinatory calculus
		* type theory
